<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,918,994,1017]" box="[151,918,994,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<typeStatus box="[151,204,994,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Type</typeStatus>
species (by present designation): 
<taxonomicName authority="Banse, 1956" authorityName="Banse" authorityYear="1956" box="[566,914,994,1017]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Fabricia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oregonica">
<emphasis box="[566,773,994,1017]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fabricia oregonica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Banse" box="[779,914,994,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Banse, K. (1956) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Gattungen Fabricia, Manayunkia und Fabriciola (Sabellidae, Polychaeta). Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 84, 415 - 438." type="journal article" year="1956">
Banse, 
<number box="[858,914,994,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1058,1458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1058,1084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Definition.</emphasis>
There is no phylogenetic hypothesis to which 
<taxonomicName box="[854,959,1058,1083]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Bansella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,959,1058,1083]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Bansella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fitzhugh" box="[1102,1297,1058,1084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Fitzhugh, K. (2008 b) Abductive inference: implications for ' Linnean' and ' phylogenetic' approaches for representing biological systematization. Evolutionary Biology, 35, 52 - 82." type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="b">
Fitzhugh 
<number box="[1217,1282,1058,1084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2008.0">2008</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
). To satisfy 
<collectionCode box="[151,220,1096,1122]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">ICZN</collectionCode>
requirements, the following list of characters form a unique combination among individuals to which this name applies: (
<number box="[394,407,1133,1159]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
) prominent, anterior peristomial ring lobe, (
<number box="[956,973,1133,1159]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
) triangular dorsal lips, (
<number box="[1274,1289,1133,1159]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="3.0">3</number>
) pigmented spermathecae in branchial lobes, (
<number box="[552,568,1170,1196]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
) inferior thoracic notochaetae narrowly hooded in all chaetigers (see also 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,265,1207,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
section below, under 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[521,1005,1207,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName authority="Banse" authorityName="Banse" box="[521,857,1207,1233]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Bansella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oregonica" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[521,754,1207,1233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Bansella oregonica</emphasis>
(Banse)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[871,1005,1207,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1058,1458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1245,1271]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus is named in honor of Dr. Karl Banse, who made numerous and significant contributions to the systematics of 
<taxonomicName box="[560,692,1282,1308]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fabriciinae">Fabriciinae</taxonomicName>
sabellids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1058,1458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1319,1345]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,429,1320,1345]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Bansella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,429,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Bansella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus, with 
<taxonomicName box="[762,913,1320,1346]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Bansella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oregonica" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[762,780,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[795,913,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">oregonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[928,1060,1320,1346]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as the only species. The purely utilitarian justification for erecting yet another monotypic genus (see also 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartman, 1951" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1951" box="[1106,1431,1357,1383]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Monroika" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1229,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Monroika</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman" box="[1238,1431,1357,1383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Hartman, O. (1951) Fabricinae (feather-duster polychaetous annelids) in the Pacific. Pacific Science, 5, 379 - 391." type="journal article" year="1951">
Hartman, 
<number box="[1365,1431,1357,1383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1951.0">1951</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cantone, 1972" authorityName="Cantone" authorityYear="1972" box="[151,510,1394,1420]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Pseudofabricia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,330,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Pseudofabricia</emphasis>
Cantone, 
<number box="[449,510,1394,1420]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzhugh, 1992" authorityName="Fitzhugh" authorityYear="1992" box="[523,861,1394,1420]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Parafabricia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[523,674,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Parafabricia</emphasis>
Fitzhugh, 
<number box="[800,861,1394,1420]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzhugh, 1998" authorityName="Fitzhugh" authorityYear="1998" box="[873,1156,1394,1420]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Brifacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[873,969,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Brifacia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fitzhugh" box="[976,1156,1394,1420]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Fitzhugh, K. (1998) New fan worm genera and species (Polychaeta, Sabellidae, Fabriciinae) from the western Pacific, and cladistic relationships among genera. Zoologica scripta, 27, 209 - 245." type="journal article" year="1998">
Fitzhugh, 
<number box="[1095,1156,1394,1420]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzhugh, 2001" authorityName="Fitzhugh" authorityYear="2001" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Raficiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1317,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Raficiba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fitzhugh" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Fitzhugh, K. (2001) A new deep-water genus and species of Fabriciinae fanworm (Polychaeta: Sabellidae) from Antarctica. Contributions in Science, Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County, 491, 8 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Fitzhugh, 
<number box="[151,211,1432,1458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) in the subfamily will be discussed below (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[720,1260,1431,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Justification for the recognition of 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1260,1431,1457]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Bansella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1154,1260,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Bansella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
